# data-models-relationships

## Core Data Models (Importance: 90/100)

The database structure centers around scope specifications with these key relationships:

1. Scope Physical Specifications
- Objective lens diameter
- Tube diameter
- Overall length
- Mount height requirements
-> Maps directly to guard configuration requirements

2. Guard Configuration Parameters
- Length thresholds based on scope measurements
- Mount compatibility rules
- Custom order indicators for non-standard specifications

## Database Schema (Importance: 85/100)

Location: scope-secure/src/lib/scope-database.ts

Primary data structures:
1. Comprehensive scope catalog
- Brand-specific configurations
- Physical dimensions
- Mount requirements

2. Guard specification mappings
- Length categories
- Compatibility matrices
- Custom configuration flags

## Relationship Maps (Importance: 95/100)

Location: scope-secure/src/lib/scope-mapping.ts

Critical relationship definitions:
1. Scope-to-Guard Mappings
- Guard length determination based on scope dimensions
- Mount height calculations using objective lens parameters
- Compatibility validation rules

2. Configuration Requirements
- Physical dimension thresholds
- Safety margin calculations
- Custom order triggers

## Product Configuration Models (Importance: 75/100)

Location: scope-secure/src/lib/constants.ts

Configuration relationships:
1. Guard Options
- Precise length measurements
- Height categories
- Mount diameter compatibility

2. Product Specifications
- Pricing tier relationships
- Subscription model mappings
- Configuration option matrices

